result.execSummary:
The defendant Darrin J Kinney was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Attempt Armed Robbery, a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(2).
  • Armed Robbery with Threat of Force [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(2).
  • Armed Robbery with Use of Force [Modifiers: Conspiracy to Commit], a class C felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Darrin J Kinney in court with Attorney John Thaddeus Wasielewski.  Defendant Darrin J Kinney in custody.  David Robles appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant has two cases before the court.

Sentencing proceeds.  State has complied with victim notification.  Statements by the State, defense counsel, Shadmeshabed K., and defendant.   COURT ADVISES the defendant he cannot possess firearms, he must provide a DNA sample and cannot vote until his civil rights are restored.  

As to Count 3:
COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE -  8  years with  Zero days credit;  -  INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT -  3 years  -  EXTENDED SUPERVISION -  5 years

As to Count 4:
COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE -  8  years with  Zero days credit; CONCURRENT to the sentence imposed as to Count 3; -  INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT -  3 years  -  EXTENDED SUPERVISION -  5 years

As to Count 7:
COURT ORDERS defendant to serve a term in the Wisconsin State Prison system - TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE -  8  years with  Zero days credit;  CONCURRENT to the sentence imposed as to Count 4;-  INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT -  3 years  -  EXTENDED SUPERVISION -  5 years

- Court sets Restitution in the amount of $100

Court advises defendant that in the event State law is changed, Court finds defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and IS eligible for the Substance Abuse Program, after 40 months of the initial confinement is served.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
-  Complete an Anger Mgmnt. program
-  Cognitive Behavior Therapy
-  Seek/Maintain full-time employment or a combination of part-time employment and school
-  Obtain GED/HSD
-  No contact with the victims
-  No contact with ALL of the co-actors
-  No weapons of any kind
-  No fine
-  Pay the costs, fees, assessments and surcharges during the term of extended supervision.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.

As to Count 4:  -  Pay Restitution in the amount of $100  to Tara P.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.  Restitution to be satisfied before the courts, fees, assessments and surcharges.

COURT ORDERS:
-  defendant to provide a biological specimen for DNA analysis, if not already done so
-  DOC to collect monetary sums/amounts at the rate of 25% of prison funds.

Appeal rights given.  Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence received and filed.  Copies given to the defendant.

Defendant Darrin J Kinney in court with attorney John Thaddeus Wasielewski.  Defendant Darrin J Kinney in custody.  David Robles appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant changes plea to GUILTY on all counts.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found that defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights. Plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty on all counts as charged in the information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Presentence Investigation Report not requested.  Defense will do a private sentencing memorandum.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for October 15, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
